TopicTitle: What does your browser suggest for Ksp related searches?

Articles.Content:
So, what does your browser suggest for Ksp related searches?

I'll go first

On google searching "Ksp was"

Results:

When was Ksp made?

ksp was ist Mechjeb

ksp 0.23 was ist neu

ksp ra gmbh was tun

P.S. Make sure you put a space after your search or the results won't be accurate

You put the letter "f" in my url/search bar and it gets swamped by the forum. ![:D](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif)

kerbin escape velocity

While looking up info on launch trajectories, I did get this rather odd suggestion.

![efa356283553cac08ed1a636e14a6931.png](http://i.gyazo.com/efa356283553cac08ed1a636e14a6931.png)

Kentucky State Police.

No, seriously.

Laythe

Top result is always the forums/main site

the results below that are always the latest news from the kentucky state police.

Kentucky State Police.

Considering my location in the midwest, that makes sense.

Since I use DuckDuckGo and it's suggestions are.. broken, to say the least, (I mainly use it as a translator using it's hashbangs (e.g !g gives me that search in google, !w wikipedia etc), i'll use google)

!g ksp add resources

!g ksp hyperedit

!g ksp high kerbin orbit
